# SamuiCam — Project Passport

## PURPOSE

Web app displaying live YouTube beach webcam streams from Koh Samui, Maldives and other tropical locations. Users build custom multi-camera layouts for Wallpaper Engine or fullscreen browser. Hosted on Netlify. No backend — pure static HTML/JS + Python maintenance scripts.

---

## ARCHITECTURE

    SamuiCam/
    ├── index.html
    │       Landing page. Hero + side nav menu.
    │       Background = live YouTube IFrame API stream.
    │       Theme toggle (dark/light), first-visit hamburger pulse.
    │
    ├── builder/index.html
    │       Camera layout builder UI.
    │       User picks cameras, order, layout mode.
    │       Generates shareable /view/ URL with params.
    │       Camera list format: { id: "VIDEO_ID" }
    │       update_streams.py rewrites these IDs automatically.
    │
    ├── view/index.html
    │       Viewer page. Reads URL params, renders iframes in grid.
    │       Contains CAM_REDIRECTS block between these exact markers:
    │           // ══ CAM_REDIRECTS — old ID → new ID ══
    │           const CAM_REDIRECTS = { "oldId": "newId" };
    │           // ══ END CAM_REDIRECTS ══
    │       update_streams.py rewrites this block automatically.
    │       Gear icon bottom-right = settings panel.
    │
    ├── config.py
    │       YOUTUBE_API_KEY only. Never commit real key.
    │
    ├── streams_config.json
    │       Source of truth for all streams.
    │       Fields per stream:
    │           primary    — original preferred video ID
    │           fallback   — backup ID (or null)
    │           current    — currently active video ID
    │           search     — YouTube search query for auto-replacement
    │           channel_id — YouTube channel ID for scoped search
    │           location   — human label
    │
    ├── update_streams.py
    │       Main maintenance script. Run manually or via cron.
    │       Flow:
    │           1. Load streams_config.json
    │           2. Check all IDs via YouTube Data API v3
    │           3. Dead stream → try fallback → search replacement
    │           4. Primary revived → restore it
    │           5. Update builder/index.html IDs
    │           6. Update view/index.html CAM_REDIRECTS block
    │           7. Save streams_config.json
    │           8. git add . && commit && push
    │
    ├── check_streams.py
    │       Read-only checker. No writes, no git.
    │       Prints live/dead status of all IDs found in HTML files.
    │       Use to diagnose before running update_streams.py.
    │
    ├── update.bat              Windows shortcut for update_streams.py
    ├── netlify.toml            Netlify deploy config
    ├── _debug_session/
    │   └── PROGRESS.md         Bug tracking log between AI sessions
    └── .claude/
        └── settings.local.json

