## KEY RULES — READ BEFORE TOUCHING ANYTHING

### Rule 1 — streams_config.json is the source of truth
- Never hardcode video IDs anywhere except here and builder/index.html
- current = what is actually playing right now
- primary = the desired original stream
- Always update current when swapping IDs
- Never rename fields — other scripts depend on exact names

### Rule 2 — builder/index.html camera list format
update_streams.py uses this regex to find and replace IDs:

    \{\s*id:\s*"([^"]+)"

Do not change this format or the regex will break.

### Rule 3 — view/index.html CAM_REDIRECTS block
Both markers must always be present in the file:

    // ══ CAM_REDIRECTS — old ID → new ID (auto-maintained by update_streams.py) ══
    const CAM_REDIRECTS = { "oldId": "newId" };
    // ══ END CAM_REDIRECTS ══

Removing or editing markers = breaking auto-update.

### Rule 4 — YouTube embed validity
A stream is valid only when BOTH conditions are true:
- embeddable = true
- liveBroadcastContent is "live" or "upcoming"

Error 153 = embed disabled by channel owner.
"gone" = deleted or private video.

### Rule 5 — No backend, no dependencies
- Pure static files. All logic is client-side JS.
- Python scripts run locally by developer only. Not on server.
- Python uses urllib only. Do NOT introduce requests or any other library.
- Frontend is vanilla HTML/CSS/JS. No npm, no frameworks, no build step.

### Rule 6 — API quota awareness
- YouTube Data API v3 has daily quota limits
- check_streams.py costs quota — use sparingly
- update_streams.py costs quota for check + search both

