## BUG FIX PROTOCOL

Before starting any fix:
1. Read _debug_session/PROGRESS.md — understand what was already done
2. Fix the bug with minimal changes
3. Update PROGRESS.md table with result

Table format:

    | # | Bug | Status | Note |
    |---|-----|--------|------|
    | 001 | description | FIXED | file:line — what changed |

Never mark a bug CONFIRMED — that is the Tyrant's job only.

---

## TECH STACK

- Frontend:   Vanilla HTML/CSS/JS — no frameworks, no build step
- Video:      YouTube IFrame API — autoplay muted, loop, no controls
- Hosting:    Netlify (static only)
- Scripts:    Python 3.12, stdlib urllib only
- VCS:        Git — update_streams.py auto-commits and pushes
- API:        YouTube Data API v3

---

## WHAT THE AI AGENT MUST NOT DO

- Must not install npm packages or introduce a build system
- Must not change regex patterns in update_streams.py without updating all call sites
- Must not remove CAM_REDIRECTS markers from view/index.html
- Must not commit config.py with a real API key
- Must not rename fields in streams_config.json
- Must not use requests library — use urllib only
- Must not mark bugs as CONFIRMED — only the Tyrant does that 
